               <p>WILLIAM DAWSON. I am a <rs id="t18250217-79-viclabel469" type="occupation">stationer</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18250217-79-victim479 t18250217-79-viclabel469"></join>, and live in Cannon-street. On the 15th of February I was going through <placeName id="t18250217-79-crimeloc470">Mitre-court, Wood-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18250217-79-crimeloc470" type="placeName" value="Mitre-court, Wood-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18250217-79-crimeloc470" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18250217-79-off467 t18250217-79-crimeloc470"></join>, and felt a tug at my coat pocket. I turned round, and saw the prisoner making away from me. I called out, and he began to run - a gentleman stopped him in Wood-street; I collared and charged him with picking my pocket - he opened his coat, and said I might search him. I said "Perhaps you have given it to somebody?" He said he had not. I took him back, and found it in the gutter, close to where I felt the tug. There was nobody near me but him.</p>
               <p>
            
